1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:03,420
<i>Dude, I want to apologize again.</i>

2
00:00:03,503 --> 00:00:05,755
<i>I was also there</i>
<i>when your mom insisted she'd stay.</i>

3
00:00:05,839 --> 00:00:07,799
<i>But you didn't say</i>
<i>to just leave her on her own.</i>

4
00:00:07,882 --> 00:00:09,926
<i>That's what Auntie Wendy said, right?</i>

5
00:00:10,010 --> 00:00:12,637
<i>If there's someone</i>
<i>who should be blamed for what's happening,</i>

6
00:00:12,721 --> 00:00:13,596
<i>it's me.</i>

7
00:00:13,680 --> 00:00:15,098
<i>Why should we blame you?</i>

8
00:00:17,517 --> 00:00:20,186
[MAGNUS]<i> Mike has a plan</i>
<i>to save all of us.</i>

9
00:00:20,270 --> 00:00:22,439
<i>If we continue walking down this path,</i>

10
00:00:22,522 --> 00:00:24,941
<i>we'll reach an old construction site.</i>

11
00:00:25,024 --> 00:00:27,485
<i>It was an old project of ours</i>
<i>that was never completed.</i>

12
00:00:27,569 --> 00:00:30,780
<i>We can use it as a hideout</i>
<i>until rescue comes.</i>

13
00:00:30,864 --> 00:00:33,033
[BOAT ENGINE WHIRRING]

14
00:00:34,075 --> 00:00:35,368
[MAGNUS] <i>This is my battle.</i>

15
00:00:35,452 --> 00:00:37,871
<i>This is our battle.</i>
<i>This is our family's battle.</i>

16
00:00:37,954 --> 00:00:39,622
- [MAGNUS]<i> It is mine.</i>
- [LIAM] <i>You know me.</i>

17
00:00:39,706 --> 00:00:40,707
<i>I'm stubborn.</i>

18
00:00:40,790 --> 00:00:42,292
<i>Since when did I listen to what you say?</i>

19
00:00:42,375 --> 00:00:44,753
<i>I won't just sit here</i>
<i>while Mama's in danger.</i>

20
00:00:46,337 --> 00:00:48,131
<i>About you and Magnus…</i>

21
00:00:48,214 --> 00:00:49,674
<i>Is it really over?</i>

22
00:00:49,758 --> 00:00:52,385
<i>Dear, I can feel it's not over yet.</i>

23
00:00:52,469 --> 00:00:55,972
[OLSEN] <i>When those animals find us,</i>
<i>let's lead them here.</i>

24
00:00:56,056 --> 00:00:57,640
<i>They'll die for sure</i>
<i>if they fall down there.</i>

25
00:00:57,724 --> 00:00:59,225
<i>That's a very good idea, Olsen.</i>

26
00:01:00,101 --> 00:01:02,228
- [SCREAMS WILDLY]
- [GUNSHOTS]

27
00:01:04,731 --> 00:01:06,775
- [GUNSHOTS]
- [MACKY SCREAMS] <i>Help!</i>

28
00:01:06,858 --> 00:01:08,568
[GUNSHOTS]

29
00:01:08,651 --> 00:01:10,737
<i>- Ice, Luna, get inside. Take cover.</i>
- [MACKY] <i>Help!</i>

30
00:01:10,820 --> 00:01:12,489
- [GUNSHOTS]
<i>- Catch him! Hurry!</i>

31
00:01:14,074 --> 00:01:17,202
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

32
00:01:19,829 --> 00:01:20,955
[GUNSHOTS]

33
00:01:21,039 --> 00:01:22,624
Help! Help!

34
00:01:22,707 --> 00:01:24,250
- [PANTING]
- [OLSEN] Sir Macky!

35
00:01:24,334 --> 00:01:26,461
- [FIN] Wait! Wait! That's a trap, sir!
- [OLSEN] Stop!

36
00:01:26,544 --> 00:01:28,505
- They're after me!
- Wait!

37
00:01:28,588 --> 00:01:30,590
If you move, you'll fall into our trap!

38
00:01:30,673 --> 00:01:33,718
- You'll be impaled, sir.
- It's a trap.

39
00:01:33,802 --> 00:01:35,303
What?!

40
00:01:35,386 --> 00:01:36,429
Wait, calm down.

41
00:01:36,513 --> 00:01:39,724
All right. Take my hand on three, okay?

42
00:01:39,808 --> 00:01:40,642
- Okay?!
- Okay!

43
00:01:40,725 --> 00:01:42,894
- One, two…
- We'll catch you.

44
00:01:42,977 --> 00:01:44,187
- Three!
- [MACKY YELPS]

45
00:01:44,270 --> 00:01:48,149
- [MACKY PANTS]
- I got you. Calm down, sir.

46
00:01:48,233 --> 00:01:54,864
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

47
00:01:54,948 --> 00:01:55,990
What was that?

48
00:01:56,074 --> 00:01:58,284
Olsen and Fin need backup.

49
00:01:58,368 --> 00:02:00,703
They found us.

50
00:02:06,126 --> 00:02:12,006
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

51
00:02:15,176 --> 00:02:17,095
[GOONS SHOUTING, SCREAMING]

52
00:02:17,178 --> 00:02:18,555
[SOUND OF IMPALED FLESH]

53
00:02:19,848 --> 00:02:21,641
- Yes! All right!
- [FIN LAUGHS]

54
00:02:21,724 --> 00:02:24,269
- [FIN] We got them!
- I told you it'd work!

55
00:02:24,352 --> 00:02:27,063
Well, are there more of them?

56
00:02:27,147 --> 00:02:28,356
Yes.

57
00:02:28,439 --> 00:02:30,150
- [FIN] There are more?
- Yes.

58
00:02:30,733 --> 00:02:31,693
Get ready.

59
00:02:31,776 --> 00:02:36,114
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

60
00:02:43,746 --> 00:02:50,753
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

61
00:03:21,159 --> 00:03:27,707
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

62
00:03:28,333 --> 00:03:31,294
[GUNSHOTS]

63
00:03:31,377 --> 00:03:33,338
[OLSEN] There's more of them!
Here they come!

64
00:03:33,421 --> 00:03:40,136
[GUNSHOTS]

65
00:03:43,389 --> 00:03:44,390
Fire!

66
00:03:44,474 --> 00:03:48,645
[GUNSHOTS]

67
00:03:48,728 --> 00:03:50,355
[MACKY GROANS]

68
00:03:50,438 --> 00:03:52,732
- Sir! Sir!
- Fin!

69
00:03:52,815 --> 00:03:57,779
- [OVERLAPPING SCREAMS]
- [GUNSHOTS]

70
00:03:57,862 --> 00:03:59,572
- [FIN] Take cover, sir!
- [MACKY GROANS]

71
00:03:59,656 --> 00:04:01,991
- [GUNSHOTS]
- [MACKY GROANING IN PAIN]

72
00:04:02,075 --> 00:04:04,035
- [GOON GASPS]
- [ICE GRUNTING]

73
00:04:04,118 --> 00:04:05,370
- Luna! Get down!
- [GUNSHOT]

74
00:04:08,957 --> 00:04:12,877
- [OLSEN GRUNTS]
- [BOTH PANTING]

75
00:04:15,838 --> 00:04:16,756
[LUNA GROANS]

76
00:04:16,839 --> 00:04:18,174
[GROANS]

77
00:04:18,258 --> 00:04:22,387
- Sir, hang in there. Hold this.
- [MACKY GROANING]

78
00:04:23,346 --> 00:04:28,142
- [THWACKING]
- [GRUNTING]

79
00:04:28,226 --> 00:04:30,061
Don't follow me! Hide!

80
00:04:30,144 --> 00:04:32,981
- [THWACKING]
- [GRUNTING]

81
00:04:33,064 --> 00:04:35,400
[GUNSHOTS]

82
00:04:35,483 --> 00:04:36,359
[ICE GRUNTS]

83
00:04:36,442 --> 00:04:38,403
[PANTING]

84
00:04:38,486 --> 00:04:40,738
[GUNSHOTS]

85
00:04:40,822 --> 00:04:41,864
[GRUNTS]

86
00:04:44,826 --> 00:04:46,244
[OLSEN SCREAMS FURIOUSLY]

87
00:04:48,079 --> 00:04:49,163
[GUNSHOTS ECHO]

88
00:04:49,247 --> 00:04:50,290
[GRUNTS]

89
00:04:50,373 --> 00:04:52,542
Grandpa!

90
00:04:54,669 --> 00:04:57,046
Grandpa! Grandpa!

91
00:04:58,589 --> 00:05:02,385
- Chief! Chief?! Chief!
- [OLSEN WAILS]

92
00:05:02,468 --> 00:05:04,137
- [GUNSHOTS]
- Chief! Chief!

93
00:05:04,220 --> 00:05:05,972
- Chief!
- No, Grandpa! No!

94
00:05:06,055 --> 00:05:07,015
Grandpa Ben!

95
00:05:07,098 --> 00:05:13,521
- [OLSEN CRIES] Why?! Grandpa!
- Pa!

96
00:05:13,604 --> 00:05:15,356
[MACKY] Rita, help me!

97
00:05:15,440 --> 00:05:16,816
Macky.

98
00:05:17,692 --> 00:05:22,238
[EMOTIONAL MUSIC PLAYING]

99
00:05:22,322 --> 00:05:25,241
- Pa!
- Why, Grandpa? Why?!

100
00:05:25,325 --> 00:05:26,326
[WENDY] Pa!

101
00:05:26,409 --> 00:05:28,494
- [OLSEN SOBS]
- Pa!

102
00:05:28,578 --> 00:05:33,708
- [OLSEN CRYING] Why did you do that?!
- Pa. Pa.

103
00:05:33,791 --> 00:05:36,711
- Why?!
- Pa!

104
00:05:36,794 --> 00:05:39,297
- Anyone! Help!
- Grandpa.

105
00:05:39,380 --> 00:05:42,467
- Please, Grandpa!
- Help! Help!

106
00:05:45,470 --> 00:05:46,721
Help!

107
00:05:46,804 --> 00:05:49,891
[OLSEN, WENDY, FIN CRYING]

108
00:05:49,974 --> 00:05:52,769
- Pa!
- Chief, hang in there!

109
00:05:52,852 --> 00:05:57,315
- I'm sorry, Grandpa!
- Wake up, Pa!

110
00:05:57,398 --> 00:05:59,108
Grandpa!

111
00:05:59,192 --> 00:06:02,445
You can't die, Grandpa!

112
00:06:02,528 --> 00:06:05,281
Why did you do that?!

113
00:06:05,364 --> 00:06:07,200
Why, Grandpa?!

114
00:06:07,283 --> 00:06:09,911
[WENDY, OLSEN CONTINUE CRYING]

115
00:06:09,994 --> 00:06:12,580
- [WENDY] Pa…
- [CRYING CONTINUES]

116
00:06:12,663 --> 00:06:14,373
[OFFICER SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY]

117
00:06:14,457 --> 00:06:17,210
[GROANING]

118
00:06:17,794 --> 00:06:20,088
Why did you do that?!

119
00:06:20,171 --> 00:06:22,006
Why?!

120
00:06:22,090 --> 00:06:24,884
[CRYING CONTINUES]

121
00:06:24,967 --> 00:06:27,261
[WENDY SOBBING] Pa!

122
00:06:27,345 --> 00:06:33,226
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

123
00:06:39,065 --> 00:06:42,068
- Where's Emil?
- [GOON] Inside, with his daughter.

124
00:06:43,653 --> 00:06:44,987
Come with me.

125
00:06:45,071 --> 00:06:46,364
We have something to do.

126
00:06:46,447 --> 00:06:53,454
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

127
00:07:07,969 --> 00:07:13,933
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

128
00:07:19,105 --> 00:07:20,898
- Boss! Boss Emil!
- [EMIL] <i>Dado.</i>

129
00:07:20,982 --> 00:07:22,775
- What's your status?
<i>- Boss!</i>

130
00:07:22,859 --> 00:07:26,904
The cops… The cops are here,
along with some soldiers.

131
00:07:26,988 --> 00:07:27,905
<i>All right.</i>

132
00:07:27,989 --> 00:07:29,907
We're ready for them.

133
00:07:38,833 --> 00:07:40,001
Dear…

134
00:07:41,752 --> 00:07:44,255
- Pa.
- Forgive me.

135
00:07:44,338 --> 00:07:48,718
But this is the only way
for you to have a chance to live.

136
00:07:48,801 --> 00:07:50,887
What are you planning, Pa?

137
00:07:53,222 --> 00:07:55,099
The cops are coming.

138
00:07:55,183 --> 00:07:57,143
If they see you,

139
00:07:57,226 --> 00:08:00,271
when they see your condition,

140
00:08:01,147 --> 00:08:04,066
I'm sure they'll take you to the hospital.

141
00:08:05,234 --> 00:08:07,278
Just surrender, Pa.

142
00:08:08,404 --> 00:08:10,239
Don't worry about me.

143
00:08:11,449 --> 00:08:13,868
We'll see each other again.

144
00:08:14,619 --> 00:08:16,329
I promise you that.

145
00:08:16,412 --> 00:08:21,876
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

146
00:08:26,422 --> 00:08:27,840
[PHONE BEEPS]

147
00:08:27,924 --> 00:08:29,550
[LINE RINGING]

148
00:08:30,426 --> 00:08:32,011
- [DADO] <i>Boss.</i>
- Dado.

149
00:08:33,095 --> 00:08:34,847
Let's go with Plan B.

150
00:08:34,931 --> 00:08:36,349
Yes, boss. Copy.

151
00:08:36,432 --> 00:08:42,480
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

152
00:08:44,565 --> 00:08:51,239
[MUSIC SWELLS]

153
00:08:58,538 --> 00:09:00,122
Emil left his daughter?

154
00:09:06,712 --> 00:09:07,922
She's still alive.

155
00:09:11,509 --> 00:09:13,386
We need to find Emil

156
00:09:14,262 --> 00:09:15,513
and get rid of him.

157
00:09:15,596 --> 00:09:16,764
Why, sir?

158
00:09:16,847 --> 00:09:19,058
Just do as I say. Don't ask questions.

159
00:09:19,141 --> 00:09:25,356
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

160
00:09:44,500 --> 00:09:46,085
- [WHISTLES]
- [LIAM GASPS]

161
00:09:50,756 --> 00:09:54,677
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

162
00:09:54,760 --> 00:09:55,845
[JERICHO] Hey.

163
00:09:56,429 --> 00:09:57,680
Have you seen Emil?

164
00:09:57,763 --> 00:09:58,764
No, sir.

165
00:10:00,224 --> 00:10:01,767
Call your comrades.

166
00:10:02,351 --> 00:10:05,021
[GOON 1] Sir,
why do you want Sir Emil dead?

167
00:10:07,189 --> 00:10:08,608
[LUCAS] Psst.

168
00:10:08,691 --> 00:10:12,945
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

169
00:10:13,029 --> 00:10:14,196
What did he say?

170
00:10:15,740 --> 00:10:17,700
That's not part of our agreement.

171
00:10:17,783 --> 00:10:20,077
My deal with Emil was clear.

172
00:10:21,162 --> 00:10:23,414
Just take the money and go.

173
00:10:23,497 --> 00:10:24,957
But what did he do?

174
00:10:25,041 --> 00:10:26,751
He didn't keep his word.

175
00:10:31,088 --> 00:10:34,050
You two can just talk it out.

176
00:10:35,968 --> 00:10:39,221
Why sentence him to death right away?

177
00:10:39,305 --> 00:10:46,187
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

178
00:10:48,481 --> 00:10:52,652
[LUCAS CHUCKLING]

179
00:10:52,735 --> 00:10:55,363
You chose the wrong side, Lucas.

180
00:10:55,446 --> 00:10:57,323
You're a fugitive now.

181
00:10:58,574 --> 00:11:00,242
As a police officer,

182
00:11:00,910 --> 00:11:02,119
I can save you.

183
00:11:03,454 --> 00:11:05,498
- Just a snap of my fingers…
- [LUCAS CHUCKLES]

184
00:11:05,581 --> 00:11:07,291
I can find a way.

185
00:11:07,375 --> 00:11:11,837
[LUCAS LAUGHING]

186
00:11:11,921 --> 00:11:15,091
Captain Jericho Jacinto.
[SNIFFS SHARPLY]

187
00:11:15,174 --> 00:11:18,010
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

188
00:11:18,094 --> 00:11:21,972
Are you sure you're still
in a position to do that?

189
00:11:23,265 --> 00:11:24,350
[LIAM] <i>Who are you talking to?</i>

190
00:11:25,684 --> 00:11:27,019
<i>Who's Jericho?</i>

191
00:11:27,728 --> 00:11:30,815
<i>He's my contact at the police station.</i>

192
00:11:32,149 --> 00:11:33,984
<i>Nothing's still happened here.</i>

193
00:11:34,068 --> 00:11:35,820
<i>We still can't get out.</i>

194
00:11:38,531 --> 00:11:40,282
[WHISPERING] Pa. Pa.

195
00:11:40,366 --> 00:11:41,784
That must be Jericho.

196
00:11:42,910 --> 00:11:45,037
The police officer Mama was talking to.

197
00:11:45,621 --> 00:11:48,541
Mama doesn't know he's working
with the hostage-takers.

198
00:11:50,084 --> 00:11:52,086
Well, they're not
on the same side anymore.

199
00:11:55,005 --> 00:11:56,590
If we get caught,

200
00:11:57,383 --> 00:12:00,678
I'll rat you out
to your fellow police officers.

201
00:12:00,761 --> 00:12:03,806
[TENSE MUSIC SWELLS]

202
00:12:03,889 --> 00:12:07,476
[GUNSHOTS]

203
00:12:07,560 --> 00:12:09,478
- He might have Mama!
- Liam!

204
00:12:09,562 --> 00:12:13,774
[GUNSHOTS]

205
00:12:13,858 --> 00:12:17,736
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

206
00:12:17,820 --> 00:12:23,242
[GUNSHOTS]

207
00:12:26,162 --> 00:12:27,455
- Let's go!
- Liam!

208
00:12:27,538 --> 00:12:32,751
[GUNSHOTS]

209
00:12:32,835 --> 00:12:39,842
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

210
00:12:44,180 --> 00:12:45,598
[PANTS]

211
00:12:54,940 --> 00:13:00,779
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

212
00:13:01,489 --> 00:13:02,865
[GRETA GRUNTS]

213
00:13:08,996 --> 00:13:15,961
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

214
00:13:17,087 --> 00:13:19,131
[JERICHO] Greta! Greta!

215
00:13:19,215 --> 00:13:21,425
- What's going on?
- We have to go.

216
00:13:21,509 --> 00:13:23,677
- Did you do what I told you?
- They've turned on me.

217
00:13:23,761 --> 00:13:26,180
- What?!
- We don't have time for this. Come on!

218
00:13:27,056 --> 00:13:29,558
- [GRETA GRUNTS]
- Don't go with him, Ma!

219
00:13:29,642 --> 00:13:31,310
He's working with those bastards!

220
00:13:31,393 --> 00:13:33,270
Liam, son…

221
00:13:33,354 --> 00:13:35,022
Get away from my mom, or I'll shoot!

222
00:13:35,105 --> 00:13:36,524
No, don't!

223
00:13:36,607 --> 00:13:38,526
He's here to help us.

224
00:13:38,609 --> 00:13:42,029
He's that Jericho guy
you talked to on the phone, right?

225
00:13:42,112 --> 00:13:44,532
Yes, he's the police officer I contacted.

226
00:13:44,615 --> 00:13:47,034
I came to this island to save you.

227
00:13:47,117 --> 00:13:49,828
I saw you talking to those bastards!

228
00:13:49,912 --> 00:13:51,664
I'm not the enemy, Liam.

229
00:13:51,747 --> 00:13:53,582
One of them almost killed you!

230
00:13:55,376 --> 00:13:57,670
You clearly betrayed each other.

231
00:13:57,753 --> 00:13:58,671
Drop your gun.

232
00:13:58,754 --> 00:14:01,924
Liam, he's our ally!
You have to believe me!

233
00:14:02,007 --> 00:14:03,676
Don't trust him, Ma!

234
00:14:04,301 --> 00:14:05,761
[JERICHO] Drop your gun.

235
00:14:05,844 --> 00:14:07,346
Listen to your mother!

236
00:14:08,764 --> 00:14:10,099
Greta.

237
00:14:10,182 --> 00:14:12,768
Explain everything to your son!

238
00:14:13,394 --> 00:14:14,520
Explain?

239
00:14:15,229 --> 00:14:19,108
Why? What do you need to explain, Ma?

240
00:14:19,191 --> 00:14:20,609
Are you really not going to drop your gun?

241
00:14:22,611 --> 00:14:23,779
- [GUNSHOT]
- [JERICHO GRUNTS]

242
00:14:23,863 --> 00:14:25,865
[GRETA GASPS, WHIMPERS]

243
00:14:25,948 --> 00:14:28,701
- Let's go, Ma! Come on!
- [GRETA WHIMPERS]

244
00:14:28,784 --> 00:14:33,873
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

245
00:14:33,956 --> 00:14:39,587
[GUNSHOTS]

246
00:14:40,754 --> 00:14:42,047
Magnus Roja!

247
00:14:42,840 --> 00:14:46,385
[GROANING, GRUNTING]

248
00:14:47,720 --> 00:14:49,179
Go on!

249
00:14:49,805 --> 00:14:50,890
Keep going!

250
00:14:51,974 --> 00:14:54,768
And I'll turn Magnus Roja into a corpse!

251
00:14:54,852 --> 00:14:58,272
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

252
00:14:58,355 --> 00:15:01,442
Drop your weapons! Hurry!

253
00:15:07,740 --> 00:15:10,075
If you don't back out,

254
00:15:10,159 --> 00:15:12,995
the owner of this island will die!

255
00:15:13,078 --> 00:15:14,455
[EMIL ON RADIO]
<i>Lucas, where are you?</i>

256
00:15:14,538 --> 00:15:15,372
Sir Emil.

257
00:15:15,456 --> 00:15:17,041
[GARBLED AUDIO] <i>We'll proceed with Plan B.</i>

258
00:15:17,124 --> 00:15:18,167
<i>Lucas, answer me.</i>

259
00:15:18,250 --> 00:15:20,210
Boss Emil, I can't hear you.

260
00:15:20,294 --> 00:15:21,921
- Boss! [GRUNTS]
- [GUNSHOTS]

261
00:15:22,004 --> 00:15:28,594
- [GUNSHOTS]
- [GRUNTING]

262
00:15:31,555 --> 00:15:33,223
- [GUNSHOT]
- [GRUNTS]

263
00:15:33,307 --> 00:15:39,730
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

264
00:15:40,397 --> 00:15:42,274
- [GUNSHOT]
- [GRUNTS]

265
00:15:42,358 --> 00:15:48,781
[GUNSHOTS]

266
00:15:55,412 --> 00:16:02,002
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

267
00:16:06,423 --> 00:16:08,592
- Tres!
- Come on!

268
00:16:08,676 --> 00:16:14,765
[GUNSHOTS]

269
00:16:16,392 --> 00:16:17,601
Let's go!

270
00:16:17,685 --> 00:16:24,358
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

271
00:16:36,370 --> 00:16:42,876
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

272
00:16:59,226 --> 00:17:06,191
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

273
00:17:12,823 --> 00:17:15,451
Hands in the air! Don't move!

274
00:17:15,534 --> 00:17:16,827
They're not moving!

275
00:17:16,910 --> 00:17:23,834
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

276
00:17:23,917 --> 00:17:29,798
[BOMB BEEPING]

277
00:17:32,009 --> 00:17:33,677
- [BOMB BEEPS RAPIDLY]
- It's a bomb!

278
00:17:33,761 --> 00:17:37,264
- [EXPLOSION]
- [GRUNTING]

279
00:17:37,347 --> 00:17:43,812
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

280
00:17:43,896 --> 00:17:44,980
[MAN GRUNTS]

281
00:17:48,358 --> 00:17:50,194
What happened? Where are they?

282
00:17:50,277 --> 00:17:52,029
They wore suicide vests.

283
00:17:52,112 --> 00:17:53,197
They exploded.

284
00:17:53,280 --> 00:17:54,782
Let's go.

285
00:17:54,865 --> 00:18:01,330
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

286
00:18:08,504 --> 00:18:11,965
- [MAGNUS GROANS]
- Hon. Hang in there, Magnus.

287
00:18:12,049 --> 00:18:14,051
You got this. [SOBS]

288
00:18:14,134 --> 00:18:16,720
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

289
00:18:20,682 --> 00:18:22,726
[REPORTER]
<i>Three hostage takers were killed</i>

290
00:18:22,810 --> 00:18:24,353
<i>after carrying out a suicide bombing.</i>

291
00:18:24,436 --> 00:18:27,147
<i>They were identified as</i>
<i>Diosdado Menor, Lucas Sebastian,</i>

292
00:18:27,231 --> 00:18:30,317
<i>and the leader of the group,</i>
<i>Emilio Padua.</i>

293
00:18:30,400 --> 00:18:33,153
[LIAM] <i>I felt angry at Papa.</i>
<i>I wanted to blame him.</i>

294
00:18:33,237 --> 00:18:34,238
<i>But then, I realized…</i>

295
00:18:34,321 --> 00:18:37,741
<i>How can I blame the man who's willing</i>
<i>to risk his entire life for his family?</i>

296
00:18:37,825 --> 00:18:39,910
[WENDY] <i>Your grandfather's</i>
<i>still in critical condition.</i>

297
00:18:39,993 --> 00:18:42,162
<i>Their deaths are not enough</i>
<i>to pay for everything.</i>

298
00:18:42,246 --> 00:18:44,414
<i>You sustained a head injury.</i>

299
00:18:45,082 --> 00:18:46,208
<i>Are you sure you're okay?</i>

300
00:18:46,291 --> 00:18:50,170
[REPORTER] <i>Is it true that</i>
<i>the hostage taking was an inside job?</i>

301
00:18:50,254 --> 00:18:52,756
<i>What matters is you're alive.</i>

302
00:18:53,257 --> 00:18:54,675
<i>We're alive.</i>

303
00:18:54,758 --> 00:18:57,094
<i>And those monsters are all dead.</i>

304
00:18:57,177 --> 00:18:59,179
<i>What about Sir Liam? How is he?</i>

305
00:18:59,263 --> 00:19:01,306
<i>Sir Magnus was shot.</i>

306
00:19:01,390 --> 00:19:03,934
<i>I don't know how he is right now.</i>

307
00:19:04,643 --> 00:19:05,477
<i>Liam?</i>

308
00:19:05,561 --> 00:19:06,520
<i>Liam!</i>

309
00:19:06,603 --> 00:19:07,855
<i>How are your parents?</i>

310
00:19:07,938 --> 00:19:10,315
<i>Mama's okay. But Papa…</i>

311
00:19:10,399 --> 00:19:11,441
<i>He was shot.</i>

312
00:19:11,525 --> 00:19:14,069
<i>He lost a lot of blood.</i>
<i>He needs a blood transfusion.</i>

313
00:19:14,153 --> 00:19:17,948
<i>Blood supplies compatible with B negative</i>
<i>have run out everywhere in Alicante.</i>

314
00:19:20,534 --> 00:19:24,329
<i>The daughter of their leader,</i>
<i>Emil Padua, is also here.</i>

315
00:19:24,413 --> 00:19:25,539
<i>I heard she's stable now.</i>

316
00:19:25,622 --> 00:19:26,748
<i>Good for her.</i>

317
00:19:27,332 --> 00:19:28,876
<i>Your grandfather's going to be okay.</i>

318
00:19:30,669 --> 00:19:32,629
<i>Doc, how's my father?</i>

319
00:19:32,713 --> 00:19:36,592
<i>We've done everything we can,</i>
<i>Mrs. Bonifacio.</i>

320
00:19:36,675 --> 00:19:40,304
[REPORTER]<i> The police are on red alert</i>
<i>right now at the said hospital.</i>

321
00:19:42,139 --> 00:19:43,307
<i>He's on his way there.</i>

322
00:19:47,853 --> 00:19:49,605
<i>I want to apologize again.</i>

323
00:19:49,688 --> 00:19:52,524
<i>We'd both do anything for our family.</i>

324
00:19:52,608 --> 00:19:56,320
[DISTORTED VOICE] <i>We won't stop</i>
<i>until we get our revenge.</i>
